secondary_outcome.description:
We will use a modified version of the WHO's definition of PPSP, to include a minimum threshold of pain severity:
Pain that began after surgery or a tissue trauma;
Pain is in an area of preceding surgery or tissue trauma;
Pain has persisted for at least three months after surgery; and
The pain is not better explained by an infection, malignancy, a pre-existing pain condition or any other alternative cause.
